<p><strong>How This Page Works:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Anyone with a relatively popular story can add their O5/O5s/Admin here.</li>
<li>Staff may edit, tweak, or remove the entry, but will not remove any entry that is in an established, popular work unless they have special reason (which must be posted on this comment page so that other staff, and the community, will judge it).
<ul>
<li>Please link entries to articles in which the O5s appear. Err on the side of linking more, not less. (<strong>Wikiwalk, have a party!</strong>)</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Anyone can also add their own entry which is not established in any story. This works like the Log of Anomalous Items &#8212; poor or flawed entries will be reworked or entirely removed at staff discretion. No explanation for removal is required &#8212; so please make it good if you're adding something.
<ul>
<li>This page starts off with an exceptionally high number of 'seed' entries which don't exist on the site. Most entries <em>should</em> be established ones to counter-balance this &#8212; but if you have a really interesting idea, don't be shy.</li>
<li>Emphasis should be placed on 'usable' characters. If your headcanon/story version is too generic, too much like what anyone could've come up with, there's no need to add them here (we've covered most of the more generic entries already, I hope).</li>
<li>Goofy characters <em>are allowed</em> if they're good. However, they should be framed as false if they get too goofy (even if they aren't meant to be) to keep character consistency &#8212; aka, the author of the page may be particularly skeptical.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Variations on specific established characters should be added to the main entry for that character and framed as &quot;conflicting reports&quot;.</li>
<li>Add new things to the bottom of the page, in order of creation. Staff may move or re-order for aesthetic purposes. (Especially popular entries should be near the top, so please feel free to request this.)
<ul>
<li>If this is judged unworkable, I recommend order of creation.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>The &quot;Dissent&quot; page is made for stuff that really skews away from standard O5 canon, such as 'they're all aliens' or 'they don't exist'. However, if you prefer to fit it into another tab, feel free.</li>
<li><span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/thedeadlymoose" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(732274); return false;">thedeadlymoose</a></span> owns this page. Any staff member has blanket permission to alter it, including other users' entries. Again, similar to the <a href="/log-of-anomalous-items">Log of Anomalous Items</a>.</li>
<li>This page is an open collaboration and should remain so. This page should never be locked except in case of ongoing troll attack.</li>
</ol>
